Q1. Given an array , return he modified array that contains the multiplication 2 of every number in the input array. (Using Map and Arrows Function)

Solution 1.a Usng normal function 
const inputArray = [1,2,3,4,5];
const newArray=[];
for(let i=0 ; i<inputArray.length;i++)
{
   newArray.push(inputArray[i]*2);
}
console.log(newArray);

Solution 1.b Uisng map
const inputArray = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];
const ans = inputArray.map((n) => {
  return n * 2;
});
console.log(ans);


Q2. Given an array return the even number from the array (Using Filters and Arrow Function)

Solution 2.a Usng normal function 
const inputArray = [1,2,3,4,5];
const newArray=[];
for(let i=0 ; i<inputArray.length;i++)
{
   if(inputArray[] % 2 == 0)
  {
        newArray.push(inputArray[i));
  }
}
console.log(newArray);

Solution 2.b Uisng Filters and Arrows Function
const inputArray = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];
const ans = inputArray.filter((n) => {
  if (n % 2 === 0) {
    return true;
  } else {
    return false;
  }
});
console.log(ans);

